  "time_ut": 1660812902,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Good price for paddy from Mandal",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Paddy harvesting in the spring season has ended in several districts and the Paddy Marketing Board decided to buy paddy at a minimum price, paying attention to the allegations made by the farmers that they are not getting a fair price for the paddy harvest.",
        "Accordingly, the price committee decided to buy 01 kg of Nadu rice at 120 rupees, 01 kg of samba rice at 125 rupees and 1 kg of Keeri samba rice at a minimum price of 130 rupees.",
        "Currently, the price of paddy in the market is less than 100 rupees, so this step was taken with the aim of giving a good price to the farmers, as some of the traders are working to buy the paddy crops of the farmers at a low price.",
        "Accordingly, although the rice purchase was scheduled to start yesterday (17th), the problems for the purchase of rice should be completed yesterday, and the purchase of rice should be formally started from today (18th), the Minister of Agriculture Mahinda Amaraweera told the Rice Marketing Board. Advised the chairman.",
        "Accordingly, out of 357 paddy warehouses in 24 districts, 55 have been kept open for the purchase of paddy, said Mr. Neil de Alwis, Chairman of the Paddy Marketing Board.",
        "These warehouses are kept open because the paddy harvest in the districts where they are located has already been harvested and harvesting has begun.",
        "But as harvesting begins in other districts, steps are being taken to open paddy warehouses in those districts.",
        "Under that, 02 Kurunegala, 02 Puttalam, 02 Trincomalee, 04 Batticaloa, 10 Ampara, 25 Anuradhapura, 01 Matale, 01 Trincomalee, 02 Kilinochchi, 02 Vavuniya, 03 Mullaitivu, 01 Polonnaruwa.",
        "The chairman also said that even now paddy is being bought from warehouses in Ampara area.",
        "The minister mentioned that the government will spend 2000 million rupees to buy paddy in the new season, and if farmers are able to sell rice at a higher price than the current price, steps should be taken to do so."
      ],
